    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn the `vim.lsp.completion` popup, documentation written in markdown is not highlighted in any way\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e69f6cce-c1d6-48a7-a0e8-69b2a3d8d539)\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nEnable completion with `vim.lsp.completion.enable()` and try to use it with any LSP that uses markdown documentation (eg. elixirls)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should be highlighted automatically, like the `vim.lsp.buf.hover` popup:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/35f7bf8c-32d6-4bc9-b77b-76df5a9712cb)\r\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev+785-g44afd0744\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 40\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nneovim-nightly COPR repo",
